        <!-- Einstein's Biography -->
        <div class="biography">
            <h2>üë®‚Äçüî¨ About Albert Einstein</h2>
            <p><strong>Born:</strong> March 14, 1879, in Ulm, Germany</p>
            
            <p><strong>Died:</strong> April 18, 1955 (at age 76) in Princeton, New Jersey, USA</p>
            
            <p><strong>How He Died:</strong> Einstein died of an abdominal aortic aneurysm. Even on his deathbed, he was still working on physics equations!</p>
            
            <p><strong>Education:</strong> Einstein struggled in school as a child but loved mathematics and physics. He attended the Swiss Federal Polytechnic School in Zurich and graduated in 1900. He couldn't find a teaching job at first and worked as a patent clerk while developing his theories!</p>
            
            <p><strong>When He Made His Discoveries:</strong> Einstein published his Special Theory of Relativity in 1905 when he was only 26 years old! This was his "miracle year" when he also explained the photoelectric effect and proved atoms exist. He published his General Theory of Relativity in 1915.</p>
            
            <p><strong>The Famous Equation E=mc¬≤:</strong> This equation shows that energy (E) equals mass (m) times the speed of light (c) squared. It means that a tiny amount of mass can be converted into a HUGE amount of energy!</p>
            
            <p><strong>Other Achievements:</strong> Einstein won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921, helped prove that atoms are real, explained why the sky is blue, and showed that light can behave as both a wave and a particle.</p>
            
            <p><strong>Legacy:</strong> Einstein's theories revolutionized our understanding of space, time, gravity, and the universe. His work made GPS satellites possible, explained black holes, and predicted gravitational waves. He's considered one of the greatest scientists of all time!</p>
        </div>

