                            <span style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 2;">
                            <strong style="color: #FFD700;">Newton vs Einstein:</strong><br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Newton:</strong> "Gravity is a mysterious force that pulls objects through space."<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong style="color: #FFD700;">Einstein:</strong> "There is no force! Objects move in straight lines through CURVED spacetime!"<br><br>
                            <strong style="color: #FFD700;">The Trampoline Analogy:</strong> Imagine space as a flat trampoline. Put a bowling ball (Sun) on it - the trampoline curves down. Now roll a marble (Earth) near it. The marble curves around the bowling ball NOT because it's being pulled, but because it's following the curved surface! That's General Relativity!
                            </span>
                        </div>

                        <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 30px;">
                            <strong>Proof Einstein Was Right:</strong><br><br>
                            <strong>1. Bending Starlight (1919):</strong> During a solar eclipse, scientists saw stars that should have been behind the Sun. The Sun's mass bent spacetime so much that starlight curved around it!<br><br>
                            <strong>2. GPS Satellites:</strong> GPS has to account for Einstein's curved spacetime. Without his corrections, GPS would be off by kilometers!<br><br>
                            <strong>3. Gravitational Waves (2015):</strong> When black holes collide, they create ripples in spacetime itself - like dropping a rock in a pond. Scientists detected these waves 100 years after Einstein predicted them!<br><br>
                            <strong>4. Black Holes:</strong> Einstein's equations predicted objects so massive they curve spacetime into a one-way trap. We've now photographed them!
                        </p>

                        <div class="fun-fact">
                            Einstein's General Relativity completely changed physics! It showed that Newton's 200-year-old gravity theory was just an approximation. Einstein revealed what gravity REALLY is - the curvature of spacetime itself! This is why he's considered one of the greatest scientists ever!
